1- write a program that takes 2 inputs from the user: weight(kg) and height(meter) and prints the BMI in the output.
BMI = weight / (square of height)

2- write a program that takes the name of the user as input and replaces all the occurrences of the character 'a' in the name with 'b' and prints it.

3- write a program that takes 2 inputs from the user as the principle amount (int) and rate of annual interest (float) and prints the expected total amount  after  2 years.

4- write a program that takes the city name from user input. irrespective of in which case the user enters the city name, print the city name in camel case meaning the first letter should be capitalized and the rest in small.
example: input: MYSORE,  print - > Mysore 

5- write a program that takes the name of the user as input and prints the index of character 'a' in the string. if 'a' is not there then return -1.

6-  Display the number of letters in the below string
my_word = "antidisestablishmentarianism"

7- take 3 inputs from the user: first name, last name, and age. Display the information in the below format 
first name: Mohit
last name: Sharma 
age 32
Display: my name is Mohit Sharma and I am 32 years old.
(note that the first letter of the first name and last name both should be in capital letters and the rest in small.)

8-take 3 inputs from the user: first name, last name, and company name. create the email alias for the user and display it.  Email alias is first 2 letters of first name, last 3 letters of last name and @company.com
example 
first name: Mohit
last name: Sharma 
company: Infosys
Display: morma@infosys.com 
(note full email id should -be in lowercase)
